---
By: Charles C. Colton
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 133
    Verse: 11
Tags:
  - Envy/Jealousy
---
Envy ought to have no place allowed it in the heart of man; for the goods of
this present world are so vile and low that they are beneath it; and those
of the future world are so vast and exalted that they are above it.
